# Yes, Exactly Right

## When You Go Live with Omise

| Action | Where | What to do |
|--------|-------|------------|
| Change secret | Cloudflare Dashboard | `PAYMENT_MODE` from `fake` → `live` |
| Add secret | Cloudflare Dashboard | Add `OMISE_SECRET_KEY` with your live key |
| **No code change** | - | Already prepared in `src/handlers/order.js` |

## Which File Has the Omise Logic

**`src/handlers/order.js`** - lines 15-30 contain the Omise API call.

## If You Switch to Kasher (Different Gateway)

**Yes, change the same file.** Update `src/handlers/order.js`:

```javascript
// Change this section (lines 15-30)
if (paymentMode === 'live') {
    // Replace Omise with Kasher API
    const response = await fetch('https://api.kasher.com/charges', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: {
            'Authorization': `Bearer ${env.KASHER_SECRET_KEY}`,
            'Content-Type': 'application/json'
        },
        body: JSON.stringify({
            amount: amount,
            currency: 'THB',
            description: `Satu donation ${orderId}`,
            channel: 'promptpay'
        })
    });
    return await response.json();
}
```

## The Swap Principle Stays the Same

| Secret | Value | What happens |
|--------|-------|--------------|
| `PAYMENT_MODE = fake` | Calls Fake Omise | Testing, no money |
| `PAYMENT_MODE = live` | Calls real gateway | Production, real money |

**Even if you rename to Kasher, keep the secret name `PAYMENT_MODE`.** Only change what "live" means in the code.

## Summary

| Gateway | File to change | New secret needed |
|---------|----------------|-------------------|
| Omise | `src/handlers/order.js` | `OMISE_SECRET_KEY` |
| Kasher | `src/handlers/order.js` | `KASHER_SECRET_KEY` |

**The swap system (one secret) remains identical.** You just rewrite the "live" section in `order.js` once.
